Sec. 60.085. HEARINGS. (a) The board may conduct hearings and
take evidence on any matter before the board.
(b) The board may appoint a hearings examiner to conduct a
hearing called by the board. The hearings examiner may be a district
employee or director.
Added by Acts 2001, 77th Leg., ch. 1393, Sec. 1, eff. June 16, 2001.

